The paper discusses the use of crowdsourcing for supervised learning, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the need for proper assessment and verification of the obtained data, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the aggregation and verification of local knowledge, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
